    "comment": "Rationale: The authors used synaptosomes derived from vGlut-Venus knockin mice to enrich for glutamatergic presynaptic terminals. Mass spectrometry was performed to detect protein content, which identified PPP2R1A. Although this method favors the detection of presynaptic proteins, postsynaptic or extrasynaptic localization of PPR2R1A cannot be excluded with this method.\n\n31/8/2017 Pim\n- Protein found under name:\nalpha isoform of regulatory subunit A, protein phosphatase 2 gi|8394027. Experimental description: Our S-synaptosome preparation was adapted from two previously published protocols (Hebb & Whittaker, 1958; Huttner et al, 1983). Briefly, forebrains of one or two mice were homogenized in 4 ml of ice-cold homogenization buffer (0.32 M Sucrose, 4 mM HEPES pH 7.4, 1 μM PMSF, 1 μg/ml Aprotinin, 1 μg/ml Leupeptin) using a 5-ml glass-Teflon homogenizer with 12 gentle strokes.",
